annotation.TEXT: So, it's finally time for Bowser's Castle...
Uh, oh...
Gee, I wonder, could there be a Yoshi coin hidden within each of these four rooms?
Let's hope I succeed on my first try here... Hmm... Nothing of interest to the right, but why would that concrete ledge be there?
And we're playing as Yoshi. Also, this is handy to know. If you press L+R anywhere in these four rooms, you'll instantly return to the lobby. That could be quite useful.
Alright, I'm back to where I left off at the end of the previous episode. (I was going to return to this point anyway, so being trapped in that endless bonus game didn't worry me.)
Yay! Now to try leaving this screen from either side...
Spin jumping off the mace may not have been strictly required, but I felt more confident doing that.
Yeah, I'm skipping that block of nine.
Wow, Bowser's actually accepting defeat rather well...
So, yeah. It's a chase scene with autoscrolling, taking me back through the room I just traversed.
So, yeah. That's what happens if you press L+R.
Huh? What's that about somebody's mother being on one of Jupiter's moons?
Ah, I guess we're Back home.
Yeah, so you do not need (or even want) to jump at all in this room!
Nope. Uh, oh. Quick, ascend!
Demo count: Farfignewton
Whoa. You don't want to dawdle anywhere!
Now, let's try taking the lower route this time.
Mechakoopas... It might be a good idea to destroy them now.

Oh, whoops! Well, will you look at that... It just so happens that this level conveniently has a built-in teleporter that I just activated. Now I can go back for that thing I missed! That was a really nice feature for WYE to include here!
No Yoshi coins, no entry. Got it. Okay, let's start with the leftmost door...
Gulp! Yaaaaahhhhh!!!!!

Hello, and welcome back to A Strange Mission! I'm back here to show what happens if you take too long to defeat Toad. Now, this footage began just a few seconds before I defeated Toad the first time, but let's see what happens if I never press up the final time...
Just for hahas. I've already established that I can do that room with just one jump.
Gah! I failed to react to that bullet appearing in time.
Also, yeah, if you're playing this yourself, you can press X to skip the credits entirely.
And that's me being an idiot. No, actually that was a demo to show you that the entirety of Bowser and his clown car are harmful to touch. (And I get a replacement power up anyway.)
Okay, we're almost there. Oh, by the way, the door you first came through doesn't open from this side, so keep going past it!
Aw, nuts. I guess I do have to use up one jump here, but it's the only jump I'll need.
Does this Warp Star take me back to the main area? Just wondering...
That door leads back to the lobby, but I need to get the Yoshi coin first.
Demo count: Still 3
And let's watch the credits roll...
Wow, I guess quite a number of people worked on this hack!
Ooh, a power up. Does this mean that if I use that convenient teleporter, I can easily farm for power ups here?
No, actually. What you're supposed to do is walk towards the right edge of the screen.
Should've taken it in for a tune up. Was the "Check engine" light lit up?
Well, there's a couple more regular coins over there.
Oh, fiddlesticks!
Ah, now here, we are limited to just three jumps. If you use them all too soon, you might get stuck (this is probably why the L+R teleporter exists in the first place).
It's a bomb! And I don't have the freedom of underwater movement! However, most of this room is quite simple. Just don't jump!
And this opens a Warp Star, but where does it lead?
You can also slide-kill the parakoopas, which might be more effective than fireballs at times.
An easy puzzle, but once again, don't be an idiot and toss the springboard up onto the upper platforms!
So, yeah. I guess we're going to be revisiting past gimmicks.
You can go under this, but only attempt it if you're small.
Okay, now for door four.
Yep, and I think I'll max out my flowers here to make up for the ones that Toad mysteriously made vanish on me in Colorful Coin Palace.
Chomp! Yep, if you take too long here, this happens... Wait, what?!
And there's yet another coin I'm not going to bother with, but I'll certainly get my fill from this multi-coin block.
Ah, another very easy puzzle.

Oh, and I tested with rewinds off camera, and if you deal the final blow before Mario falls off the screen, the level will proceed normally, so I guess after Mario fell off screen, the game treated Mario as being on a different screen when the screen exit activated, sending me to level 0.
And now for door number three.
...D'oh! No I can't, because this footage was started from the middle of my first trip through the level, so the level hasn't been completed yet! ...Sigh... One moment please.
Well, good thing for that convenient teleporter! And, yeah. You can just warp back to the lobby as soon as you collect the Yoshi coin. You don't have to actually use the door to get back.
Oh, by the way, don't throw that springboard up to the higher ledge, or you'll get stuck and be forced to use that convenient teleporter.
So, yeah. I'm stuck. But, not really, as I can just Start+Select out...
Thwomps. Meh.
Whoa, careful there! Only the bottom of Yoshi's shoes are muncher-proof!

Honestly, I think the credits are scrolling kind of slowly, so I'll double the speed of this part. You should still be able to read them with little trouble (and you can always pause if they're going too fast for you).

Also, by the way, I probably would've uploaded this video yesterday, but I wanted to watch HCBailly's Yiazmat video, and that took about two and a half hours, which limited my remaining available time.
Uh, oh. I'm being forced to walk to the left. Oh, hey there Bowser. How's it going?
Anything down here? Ehh... I'm not going to risk it. Let's stay on the "intended" path.
Interesting... When I hit L+R right after getting that previous flower, my colors continued cycling for a split second after I returned to the lobby.
Well, I found the Yoshi coin. Now I just gotta reach it...
Whoa! I almost got a bullet in my gut! But yeah, going over there triggers the next cutscene.
Now, honestly, I think this level could use a midpoint here, because if you fail now, you have to redo all of those Yoshi coin rooms, which is annoying.
Man, if only I were big... Well, I'm not going to go out of my way for every single coin anyway.
Wow, that's weird. It looked like I managed to enter that goozack when I wasn't lined up with it at all.
Alright, so is Toad ever going to summon anything besides coins?
Thwimp. Meh.
Uh, oh. Parakoopas. Fireballs can help here, but due to some weird glitch, they vanish when they hit a sloped conveyor belt (this is true in the original game, too).
Haven't you learned yet, Bowser? Mario will always reach your castle in some way, shape, or form!
Yay, now my OCD can relax.
Forget it. Those coins aren't worth the trouble.
Now, I wonder if I can complete this whole room without jumping at all. I forget if that's possible...
Of course, you could just try to jump an additional 252 times to get unstuck in such a situation too, but that would kind of go against the theme of the level, and it would be very tedious.
Whoa, that was a sort of lucky stomp.
And I guess that's it. Well this has been a decent somewhat short hack.
Umm... And is that it, Bowser? The chase just stops here? ...Is this game stuck?
Alright, now to travel through all of these goozacks!
Umm... I hit up after Mario fell off the screen, and it still dealt the final blow to Toad, but then I ended up here!
I wonder if maybe I should've saved that power up for later...
Gulp! Quadruple gulp! Gulp!

Whoa, bullet. Now, this part could be potentially tricky. You've got to fall onto the note block, then land on the ledge to the right. However, don't use the jump button at all for this, or you'll probably blow!
Alright, now before I leave, is there anything down there?

Yep. Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through A Strange Mission! It might be a while before I start another thing, and I'm not entirely sure what I'll do next (I was thinking of trying the SMW hack "COLORS", but Goron50 just did that one). Well, I'm sure I'll think of something. See ya!
Some somewhat tricky jumps, but nothing too ridiculous...
Also, there's random bullets, so watch out for those.
Uhh... There's munchers approaching! What do I do? Mario, don't just stand there like an idiot! Quick, press up!
Loads of goozacks! (Let's see if anyone gets that reference.)
Wait, did I miss something down below? Yeah, I did, and I kind of want it, or else my OCD will bother me.
Huh. I thought I saw something to the right for a split-second there. Well, whatever. Hey, Bowser, I've got the four Yoshi coins, so open up!
